We observed considerable phenotypic variation among lines and across environments, visualized by (A) histograms of phenotypic values in each location (colors, shaded by year). (B) Phenotypic plasticity was measured by regressing phenotypic values on the mean in each environment (colored points corresponding to locations) and calculating the slope of the regression line (bi
, linear plasticity) and deviations from that line (σδ

(

i

), nonlinear plasticity). Different patterns of genotypic response were observed for each trait, including more stable (red) or plastic (blue) genotypes. (C) Correlations between the genotype mean (gi
) and the slope were often positive, but (D) no correlation was observed between the genotype mean and the deviation.

